WEBVTT

00:01.500 --> 00:03.542
Announcer: PREVIOUSLY ON
DAWSON'S CREEK...

00:03.542 --> 00:04.959
I DON'T THINK
YOU'RE ANGRY WITH ME

00:04.959 --> 00:06.000
FOR KISSING YOU.

00:06.000 --> 00:06.667
I THINK YOU'RE
ANGRY WITH YOURSELF

00:06.667 --> 00:08.708
FOR KISSING ME BACK.

00:08.708 --> 00:09.834
YOU KISSED MY GIRLFRIEND.

00:09.834 --> 00:10.917
THE TRUTH IS
I'D DO IT AGAIN.

00:10.917 --> 00:11.834
KISS ME.

00:11.834 --> 00:13.000
I THOUGHT
YOU'D NEVER ASK.

00:13.000 --> 00:14.875
Joey:
YOU MAKE ME SO HAPPY,

00:14.875 --> 00:17.208
BUT I HAVE TO MAKE
MYSELF HAPPY FIRST.

00:17.208 --> 00:20.000
WE CAN'T JUST SAY
I LOVE YOU FOR THE FIRST TIME

00:20.000 --> 00:21.000
AND HAVE IT BE OVER!

00:21.000 --> 00:21.291
GOOD NIGHT.

00:32.500 --> 00:35.291
Woman [ON TV]:
I TRUST I MAY HAVE LEAVE
TO SPEAK, AND SPEAK I WILL.

00:35.291 --> 00:38.500
Dawson: THERE'S NOT
A SINGLE DRAMATIC
STORY LINE IN EXISTENCE

00:38.500 --> 00:40.375
THAT SHAKESPEARE
DIDN'T CONQUER FIRST.

00:40.375 --> 00:43.000
FAMILY REVENGE,
POLITICAL INTRIGUE,
THE GREAT GENDER BATTLE.

00:43.000 --> 00:45.375
THE GUY MAPPED IT
ALL OUT FOR US.

00:45.375 --> 00:46.834
AND WHAT WAS
HIS PARTING LESSON?

00:46.834 --> 00:49.000
WHAT GENRE OF ALL GENRES
DID HE FINALLY ARRIVE AT

00:49.000 --> 00:53.375
AFTER YEARS OF TOIL
AND SACRIFICE? TRAGEDY.

00:53.375 --> 00:54.208
SHH!

00:54.208 --> 00:55.875
LIKE ALL GREAT ROMANTICS,

00:55.875 --> 00:59.708
HE FINALLY REALIZED
THAT LIFE WAS A LOT
MORE LIKELY TO END UP

00:59.708 --> 01:02.166
WITH A BUNCH OF DEAD
DANISH PEOPLE ON STAGE
THAN WITH A KISS.

01:04.375 --> 01:05.208
WHAT A SAD MOVIE.

01:05.208 --> 01:07.667
MOM, YOU CRIED
AT COMMERCIALS.

01:07.667 --> 01:09.625
ONLY THAT
COTTON COMMERCIAL.

01:09.625 --> 01:12.792
WE HAVE TO DO SOMETHING
ABOUT YOUR PERPETUAL
STATE OF MELANCHOLY.

01:12.792 --> 01:15.542
I'M CONCERNED ABOUT YOU.

01:15.542 --> 01:19.959
WELL, HONEY,
I'M CONCERNED ABOUT YOU.

01:19.959 --> 01:21.792
EVER SINCE
YOUR BREAKUP WITH JOEY,

01:21.792 --> 01:23.166
YOU HAVEN'T SAID
ONE WORD ABOUT IT.

01:23.166 --> 01:26.917
DAWSON, YOU HAVEN'T
EVEN WALLOWED.

01:26.917 --> 01:28.583
WHAT GOOD
IS WALLOWING?

01:28.583 --> 01:31.125
ALL THE WALLOWING
IN THE WORLD DOESN'T
BRING SOMEONE BACK.

01:31.125 --> 01:32.250
WALLOWING ISN'T
ABOUT GETTING THEM BACK.

01:32.250 --> 01:35.583
IT ISN'T ABOUT THEM AT ALL.
IT'S ABOUT YOU.

01:35.583 --> 01:37.542
AND LEARNING
TO ALLOW YOURSELF

01:37.542 --> 01:40.917
THE FEW MEAGER ADVANTAGES
OF BEING THE DUMPEE.

01:40.917 --> 01:42.583
ADVANTAGES?

01:42.583 --> 01:47.166
SURE, LIKE ALLOWING YOURSELF
TO STUFF YOUR FACE

01:47.166 --> 01:50.417
WITH A LIFETIME SUPPLY OF
RED LICORICE AND DOUGHNUTS.

01:50.417 --> 01:54.834
OR, UM, A NEWFOUND
APPRECIATION
FOR COUNTRY MUSIC.

01:54.834 --> 01:58.208
LIKE AN EXCUSE TO WATCH
THAT LAST SCENE
FROM FIELD OF DREAMS.

01:58.208 --> 02:01.708
ACQUIRING THE NECESSARY
PAIN TO WRITE
BAD, BITTER POETRY.

02:01.708 --> 02:02.959
A REASON TO SCOWL.

02:02.959 --> 02:03.917
A REASON TO BITCH!

02:03.917 --> 02:04.959
WORK OUT AGGRESSION.

02:04.959 --> 02:06.041
YEAH! YOU SEE,

02:06.041 --> 02:08.125
WHEN YOU THINK
ABOUT IT, HONEY,

02:08.125 --> 02:12.083
EVERY INCH OF PAIN
THAT TOUCHES YOU

02:12.083 --> 02:14.250
MAKES YOU A DEEPER,
MORE REAL INDIVIDUAL.

02:14.250 --> 02:19.959
WHETHER YOU'RE 15 OR...
SLIGHTLY OLDER.

02:19.959 --> 02:22.417
SO IT DOESN'T
GET ANY EASIER?

02:22.417 --> 02:26.291
NOPE. YOU JUST
GO TO BED EARLIER.

02:26.291 --> 02:28.208
NIGHT, HONEY.

02:28.208 --> 02:29.667
GOOD NIGHT, MOM.

02:29.667 --> 02:34.125
UM, HOPE I WAS AN
ACCEPTABLE SUBSTITUTE
FOR MOVIE NIGHT.

02:34.125 --> 02:36.166
YOU DID GREAT.

04:04.834 --> 04:08.542
"WHAT LIGHT THROUGH
YONDER WINDOW BREAKS?"

04:08.542 --> 04:12.458
IT IS THE MIDTERM.

04:12.458 --> 04:17.791
AND YOUR IMPENDING FAILURE
IS BUT HOURS AWAY.

04:17.791 --> 04:20.333
BLUE BOOKS.

04:20.333 --> 04:22.083
YOU'LL NOTICE
THEY ARE BLANK.

04:22.083 --> 04:24.917
AND FOR MANY OF YOU,

04:24.917 --> 04:30.792
THEY'LL SCORE HIGHER AS SUCH
THAN WHEN ACTUALLY WRITTEN IN.

04:30.792 --> 04:32.667
PLEASE SIGN YOUR REAL NAME,
AHEM.

04:32.667 --> 04:36.417
AS FOR THE TEST, AHEM,
IT WILL COVER EVERYTHING

04:36.417 --> 04:39.333
WE HAVE STUDIED IN
ENGLISH LITERATURE THUS FAR

04:39.333 --> 04:45.834
AND WILL BE WORTH 50%
OF THIS TERM'S GRADE.

04:47.583 --> 04:50.750
MAIN POINTS OF INTEREST:
SHAKESPEARE, DICKENS,
THE ROMANTICS,

04:50.750 --> 04:55.750
AND YOUR FAVORITE--THE READ
EVERYBODY'S TALKING ABOUT--

04:55.750 --> 04:56.750
BEOWULF.

05:01.250 --> 05:04.959
I WILL BE HOSTING
A STUDY SESSION

05:04.959 --> 05:06.917
IN THIS CLASSROOM
AT 3:00.

05:06.917 --> 05:09.000
IT IS MY RECOMMENDATION
YOU ATTEND,

05:09.000 --> 05:11.375
UNLESS,
OF COURSE, YOUR PARENTS

05:11.375 --> 05:16.542
HAVE DEDICATED
A EAST WING OR TWO TO
AN IVY LEAGUE INSTITUTION,

05:16.542 --> 05:21.125
IN WHICH CASE YOUR TRAGIC,
EAST COAST ARISTOCRATIC,
SOCIAL ALCOHOLIC FATE

05:21.125 --> 05:24.792
HAS ALREADY BEEN SEALED.

05:24.792 --> 05:27.500
THIS IS MORE THAN
JUST AN EXAM, PEOPLE.

05:29.959 --> 05:31.125
IT'S YOUR LIFE.

05:31.125 --> 05:33.667
[BELL RINGING]

05:35.708 --> 05:36.542
HEY.

05:38.792 --> 05:41.834
DAWSON, AT SOME POINT
WE HAVE TO SAY SOMETHING
TO EACH OTHER.

05:41.834 --> 05:43.250
WHAT WOULD YOU
LIKE ME TO SAY, JOEY?

05:43.250 --> 05:45.208
WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO SAY?

05:45.208 --> 05:46.792
GO AWAY.

05:48.000 --> 05:50.333
BESIDES THAT.

05:50.333 --> 05:53.250
JOEY, YOU MADE IT VERY CLEAR
YOU NEEDED SPACE, OK?

05:53.250 --> 05:54.834
I AM GIVING YOU THAT SPACE.

05:54.834 --> 05:56.000
I DIDN'T THINK
IT WOULD MEAN

05:56.000 --> 05:58.500
WE'D BE CUTTING OFF
ALL COMMUNICATION,
DAWSON.

05:58.500 --> 06:00.250
WHAT DID YOU THINK,
IT WOULD MEAN, JOEY?

06:00.250 --> 06:01.333
THIS ISN'T FAIR.

06:01.333 --> 06:02.291
TO WHICH ONE OF US?

06:02.291 --> 06:03.834
YOU CAN'T MAKE UP
ALL THE RULES!

06:03.834 --> 06:04.792
I DON'T WANT TO.

06:04.792 --> 06:06.417
THEN WHAT
DO YOU WANT?!

06:14.125 --> 06:16.250
ONE DAY THIS CAFETERIA
IS DESTINED

06:16.250 --> 06:17.583
TO COOK A FRY THAT
ACTUALLY TASTES LIKE A FRY.

06:17.583 --> 06:21.542
MéNAGE Ä TROIS.
EVER BEEN IN ONE?

06:21.542 --> 06:25.250
ALL HAIL, THE QUEEN
OF NON SEQUITURS HAS SPOKEN.

06:25.250 --> 06:27.792
IT'S NOT A NON SEQUITUR.
IT'S THIS MONTH'S JANE.

06:27.792 --> 06:29.667
CHICK MAGAZINES
ARE RACIER THAN PLAYBOY.

06:29.667 --> 06:31.333
THERE'S ALWAYS
SOME ARTICLE IN THERE

06:31.333 --> 06:33.458
ABOUT HOW
TO PROLONG YOUR THIS
OR AROUSE YOUR THAT.

06:33.458 --> 06:34.792
THIS ONE'S
A PURITY TEST.

06:34.792 --> 06:36.708
WHAT?

06:36.708 --> 06:38.875
PURITY TEST.
YOU'VE HEARD OF 'EM.

06:38.875 --> 06:40.375
AN ASSORTMENT
OF SEXUAL QUESTIONS

06:40.375 --> 06:43.375
WHICH WHEN TOTALED IS
MEANT TO GAUGE THE LEVEL
OF SEXUAL EXPERIENCE.

06:43.375 --> 06:46.083
OKEY-DOKEY. TIME
TO PUT THAT AWAY NOW.

06:46.083 --> 06:48.375
WHY? IT'S FUN.

06:48.375 --> 06:50.625
GAUGING OUR LEVEL
OF SEXUAL EXPERTISE

06:50.625 --> 06:54.166
IS NOT REALLY MY IDEA
OF JOY ABOUNDING.

06:54.166 --> 06:58.083
DON'T THINK I DON'T KNOW
WHAT THIS IS ABOUT,
PACEY WITTER.

06:58.083 --> 07:00.125
I KNOW YOUR HISTORY.

07:00.125 --> 07:01.667
YOU DO?

07:01.667 --> 07:04.250
SURE. YOU'RE
A TYPICAL GUY.

07:04.250 --> 07:05.750
YOU WANT EVERYONE
TO THINK

07:05.750 --> 07:10.917
YOU HAVE THIS UNSEEMLY,
ADVENTUROUS
SEXUAL EXISTENCE

07:10.917 --> 07:12.834
WHEN IN FACT
YOUR PURITY LEVEL

07:12.834 --> 07:16.000
IS PROBABLY CLOSER
TO BIG BIRD'S
THAN BILL CLINTON'S.

07:17.291 --> 07:19.375
YEAH, YOU KNOW WHAT,
YOU GOT ME.

07:19.375 --> 07:21.917
THAT'S ME, MR.
EMBARRASSINGLY PURE.

07:21.917 --> 07:24.750
WHATEVER. SO, AM I
GONNA SEE YOU AT
PETERSON'S CRAM-O-RAMA?

07:24.750 --> 07:26.333
THAT WOULD IMPLY
THAT I AM GOING.

07:26.333 --> 07:29.208
NO, NO, PACEY,
YOU CANNOT BAIL
ON THIS STUDY SESSION.

07:29.208 --> 07:30.250
WAY TOO IMPORTANT.

07:30.250 --> 07:31.250
TO YOU.

07:31.250 --> 07:33.708
TO ANYONE WHO CARES
ABOUT THEIR GRADE.

07:33.708 --> 07:34.417
WELL, SEE,
THERE'S THE RUB.

07:34.417 --> 07:36.625
YO SOY
NOT CONCERNED.

07:36.625 --> 07:37.708
DON'T JOKE ABOUT THIS.
I'M SERIOUS.

07:37.708 --> 07:39.625
AS COMMITTED AS YOU ARE
TO DOING EVERYTHING

07:39.625 --> 07:42.000
WITHIN YOUR POWER
TO GETTING AN "A,"

07:42.000 --> 07:43.959
I AM EQUALLY COMMITTED
TO GETTING MY "C."

07:43.959 --> 07:45.875
POSSIBLY "D" IF I
CAN'T GET A GOOD LOOK
AT YOUR ANSWER SHEET.

07:45.875 --> 07:47.750
PACEY.

07:47.750 --> 07:50.458
GIVE ME ONE GOOD REASON
WHY I SHOULD.

07:50.458 --> 07:51.792
ME.

07:55.750 --> 07:57.500
OK. FINE. I'LL GO.

07:57.500 --> 08:00.750
JUST DON'T EXPECT ME
TO STAY AWAKE.

08:00.750 --> 08:03.041
JEN-A-LISH, DELISH.

08:03.041 --> 08:05.458
HEY, CHRIS.
WHAT'S UP?

08:05.458 --> 08:06.542
LONG RUN TODAY.

08:06.542 --> 08:07.458
YEAH.

08:07.458 --> 08:08.500
THOUGHT YOU'D BE LOOKING

08:08.500 --> 08:10.166
FOR SOMEONE
TO KEEP STRIDE WITH.

08:10.166 --> 08:12.417
AND YOU'D LIKE
TO BE THAT SOMEONE?

08:12.417 --> 08:14.458
I'M A GOOD PACER.

08:14.458 --> 08:16.500
I KNOW WHEN TO SPEED UP
AND WHEN TO SLOW DOWN.

08:16.500 --> 08:19.000
AND WHEN
TO LEAVE SOMEONE ALONE?

08:19.000 --> 08:21.583
JEN, IS THERE
A PARTICULAR REASON

08:21.583 --> 08:23.834
WHY YOU'RE NOT RECEPTIVE
TO MY WILY CHARMS?

08:23.834 --> 08:26.667
OTHER THAN THE FACT THAT
YOU EMIT THEM REGULARLY

08:26.667 --> 08:29.041
TO ANY SKIRT
WITHIN A 6-MILE RADIUS?

08:29.041 --> 08:30.000
ACTUALLY, I HAVE A CAR,

08:30.000 --> 08:31.917
SO IT'S MORE LIKE
THE TRI-STATE AREA.

08:31.917 --> 08:34.375
AHA. A SMILE.

08:34.375 --> 08:35.958
MISSION ACCOMPLISHED.

08:35.958 --> 08:37.958
[SIGHS]

08:37.958 --> 08:38.792
LATER, CHRIS.

08:48.333 --> 08:51.000
AND THE HAWK CIRCLES.

08:51.000 --> 08:53.500
HE'S JUST BEING CUTE,

08:53.500 --> 08:55.250
WHICH HE REALLY IS.

08:55.250 --> 08:57.917
YOU SEEN HIS LOVE 'EM
AND LEAVE 'EM RAP SHEET?
IT'S EPIC.

08:57.917 --> 08:59.375
RELAX, DAWSON.

08:59.375 --> 09:01.166
JUST LOOKING OUT.

09:01.166 --> 09:03.792
SO, YOU HITTING
THAT STUDY SESSION?

09:03.792 --> 09:05.083
OH. I DOUBT IT.

09:05.083 --> 09:09.625
I'M NOT MUCH IN
THE "APPLYING MYSELF"
ZONE THESE DAYS.

09:09.625 --> 09:11.000
HOW ABOUT YOU?

09:11.000 --> 09:12.375
WELL, IT'S EITHER THAT

09:12.375 --> 09:15.708
OR ANOTHER EVENING
WATCHING SOME AWFUL,
SEVENTIES TEARJERKER

09:15.708 --> 09:17.708
WITH MY MOTHER,
SO...YOU SHOULD GO.

09:20.208 --> 09:22.041
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT,
DAWSON.

09:22.041 --> 09:23.917
SINCE IT DOESN'T LOOK
LIKE I'LL BE HAVING

09:23.917 --> 09:27.083
A HOT NIGHT OF UNBRIDLED
PASSION WITH ROMEO
OVER THERE,

09:27.083 --> 09:28.708
I'LL CONSIDER IT.

09:28.708 --> 09:29.875
ALL RIGHT.

09:31.000 --> 09:32.083
"DEAR CLASS,
WENT HOME WITH A COLD

09:32.083 --> 09:35.542
"THAT WAS CONSIDERABLY
MORE IMPORTANT THAN YOU.

09:35.542 --> 09:37.583
"THE TEST IS STILL ON
FOR TOMORROW.

09:37.583 --> 09:38.917
"STUDY THE SAMPLE QUESTIONS.

09:38.917 --> 09:41.708
UNTIL THEN, HARDLY YOURS,
MR. PETERSON."

09:41.708 --> 09:45.417
SO HE BAILED ON HIS
OWN SESSION. GREAT.

09:45.417 --> 09:47.417
WE SHOULD HAVE
OUR OWN STUDY SESSION.

09:47.417 --> 09:49.125
MY FOLKS ARE
IN SAINT MARTIN.

09:49.125 --> 09:50.834
WE'LL HAVE THE WHOLE
HOUSE TO OURSELVES.

09:50.834 --> 09:52.583
LIKE WE'D GET A LOT
OF WORK DONE THAT WAY.

09:52.583 --> 09:55.083
THE LADY QUESTIONS
MY MOTIVES?

09:55.083 --> 09:57.166
INVITE YOUR FRIENDS.

09:57.166 --> 09:58.417
YOU TWO INTERESTED?

09:58.417 --> 10:01.000
LET'S STUDY AT MY PLACE.

10:01.000 --> 10:04.125
I WAS THINKING MORE
ALONG THE LINES OF
THE CITY LIBRARY.

10:04.125 --> 10:07.083
WHOA, WHOA. HIS OFFER
DOES HAVE A CERTAIN
ENTICING QUALITY.

10:07.083 --> 10:10.250
SINCE WHEN HAVE YOU
BEEN IN SUCH A RUSH
TO FORM A STUDY GROUP?

10:10.250 --> 10:12.083
HAVE YOU EVER
SEEN THIS MAN'S HOUSE?

10:12.083 --> 10:14.250
HIS FAMILY
IS TOTALLY LOADED.

10:14.250 --> 10:16.208
THEY GOT
A SATELLITE DISH.

10:16.208 --> 10:19.125
OH, COME ON.

10:19.125 --> 10:20.917
ALL RIGHT. WE'RE IN.

10:20.917 --> 10:22.667
COOL.
I'LL DRIVE.

10:24.750 --> 10:25.750
YOUNG LADY.

10:25.750 --> 10:28.417
WILL YOU
JOIN US?

10:28.417 --> 10:30.041
HOW CAN I RESIST?

10:35.959 --> 10:38.959
Andie: HEY, JOEY.
SO WHAT ARE YOUR STUDY PLANS?

10:38.959 --> 10:41.667
OH, JUST ME, MY ENGLISH LIT
BOOK, AND A LOUD, CRYING BABY.

10:41.667 --> 10:43.625
GOOD. THEN YOU CAN
COME WITH ME.

10:43.625 --> 10:44.917
WHERE?

10:44.917 --> 10:47.834
A STUDY SESSION AT CHRIS
WOLFE'S. I CAN'T DO THIS ALONE.

10:47.834 --> 10:51.041
CHRIS WOLFE'S? YOU'RE GOING TO
RELY ON CHRIS WOLFE TO PROVIDE A
SUITABLE STUDY ENVIRONMENT?

10:51.041 --> 10:54.166
I THINK I'M BETTER OFF
WITH THE LOUD, CRYING BABY.

10:54.166 --> 10:56.458
OK, DO YOU HONESTLY
BELIEVE I WOULD LET THIS NIGHT

10:56.458 --> 10:58.708
BE ANYTHING LESS THAN
RIDICULOUSLY BENEFICIAL?

10:58.708 --> 11:01.834
TRUST ME. I'M IN MEGA-CONTROL
OF THIS EVENT.

11:03.000 --> 11:05.250
HEY DAWSON! WHERE YOU
HEADED LITTLE BUDDY?

11:05.250 --> 11:08.375
WELL, SKIPPER, I SAW PETERSON'S
NOTE. I'M HEADED HOME.

11:08.375 --> 11:12.333
I'M ACTUALLY HEADED TO A
DIFFERENT STUDY SESSION, IF
YOU'RE UP FOR IT.

11:12.333 --> 11:13.500
"DIFFERENT STUDY SESSION"?

11:13.500 --> 11:15.000
IS THIS PACEY WITTER CODE
FOR PARTY?

11:15.000 --> 11:16.500
BROTHEL? ROAD TRIP
TO DISNEYLAND?

11:16.500 --> 11:19.000
BELIEVE IT OR NOT, THIS IS A
TRUE MEETING OF INTELLECTUALS

11:19.000 --> 11:23.417
IN A HIGHLY MODERATED STUDIOUS
ENVIRONMENT AND THAT, MY FRIEND,
IS OUR RIDE.

11:23.417 --> 11:24.500
[HONKS HORN]

11:24.500 --> 11:25.166
Pacey: SO WHAT DO YOU SAY?

11:25.166 --> 11:27.333
SURE.

12:03.917 --> 12:05.917
UH, THE TV IS THAT WAY.

12:05.917 --> 12:08.542
THE JACUZZI AND SAUNA
ARE OUT BACK.

12:08.542 --> 12:10.000
WE KEEP EXTRA SUITS IN THE
GUEST ROOM,

12:10.000 --> 12:12.708
AND, UH, KITCHEN'S THAT WAY
IF YOU GET HUNGRY.

12:12.708 --> 12:15.250
SOUNDS LIKE WE'RE GOING
TO GET A LOT OF STUDYING DONE.

12:15.250 --> 12:18.458
REMINDER, I'M IN
COMPLETE CONTROL HERE.

12:18.458 --> 12:20.375
[CLEARS THROAT]

12:20.375 --> 12:23.667
EVERYONE, MY LITTLE SISTER,
DINA.

12:24.917 --> 12:27.917
SHE PROMISES TO STAY
OUT OF THE WAY.

12:27.917 --> 12:30.333
NOPE. THIS ROOM ISN'T
GONNA DO.

12:30.333 --> 12:32.542
WE'RE GONNA NEED A LONG
TABLE, PROPER LIGHTING,

12:32.542 --> 12:34.375
AND HIGH-BACKED CHAIRS.

12:36.333 --> 12:37.750
WHERE'S PACEY?

12:38.750 --> 12:40.500
HEY, CHECK THIS OUT.

12:40.500 --> 12:41.583
TWO HUNDRED CHANNELS FROM
ALL OVER THE WORLD.

12:41.583 --> 12:42.917
IT'S A COUCH POTATO'S DREAM.

12:42.917 --> 12:46.083
LOOK AT THAT!
3 STOOGES  IN CANTONESE.

12:46.083 --> 12:50.917
WHY DO YOU INSIST ON UNDERMINING
ME AT EVERY OPPORTUNITY YOU GET?

12:50.917 --> 12:53.667
THINK OF HOW BORING
THE ALTERNATIVE IS.

12:53.667 --> 12:56.333
LOOK, I'M GOING TO NEED YOUR
HELP WITH OUR ATTENTION DEFICIT
HOST, OK?

12:56.333 --> 12:59.917
THERE'S NO WAY I CAN EXPEND
ENERGY ROUNDING UP THE BOTH OF
YOU.

12:59.917 --> 13:00.917
NOW, COME ON!

13:00.917 --> 13:03.750
[WHINING]
BUT I WANNA WATCH TV.

13:03.750 --> 13:05.458
SO, THE PLAN OF ATTACK
IS SIMPLE.

13:05.458 --> 13:08.166
USING THIS BOOK, WE'LL SPEND 30
MINUTES ON EACH OF THE VARIOUS
SECTIONS:

13:08.166 --> 13:11.834
VICTORIAN POETRY, SHAKESPEARE,
DICKENS, ETC.

13:11.834 --> 13:15.917
AND, BY MY WATCH, IF WE ALLOW
FOR A FEW 15 MINUTE BREAKS,

13:15.917 --> 13:18.917
WE'LL BE ABLE TO COVER THE
ENTIRE COURSE LOAD BY MIDNIGHT.

13:18.917 --> 13:23.125
THAT WILL STILL GIVE US ENOUGH
TIME TO DO AN HOUR SPEED ROUND
AND GET A GOOD NIGHT'S SLEEP.

13:23.125 --> 13:24.250
SOUND GOOD?

13:28.625 --> 13:29.959
UH, ANYBODY WANNA ORDER PIZZA?

13:29.959 --> 13:31.959
Joey: ME.
ABSOLUTELY, YEAH.

13:31.959 --> 13:34.959
HEY, I GOT IT!

13:34.959 --> 13:40.792
LISTEN, WHY DON'T YOU JUST THINK
OF THIS AS SEVERAL OF OUR 15
MINUTES BREAKS STRUNG TOGETHER?

13:40.792 --> 13:44.875
GOT A BOTTLE IN HERE FROM '84.
IT'S FROM NAPA.

13:45.458 --> 13:47.083
FANCY.

13:47.083 --> 13:49.542
WELL, ACTUALLY THE WINE IS MADE
BY A MARRIED COUPLE

13:49.542 --> 13:53.041
WHO HAVE SORT OF A MOM-AND-POP
